SIMPLE: monstrous
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monstrous
<hw>Mon"strous</hw> <pr>(m⟦ocr⟧n"str⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[OE. <ets>monstruous</ets>, F. <ets>monstrueux</ets>, fr. L.
<ets>monstruosus</ets>, fr. <ets>monstrum</ets>. See
<er>Monster</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Marvelous; strange.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having the qualities of a monster; deviating greatly
from the natural form or character; abnormal; <as>as, a
<ex>monstrous</ex> birth</as>.</def> <rj><au>Locke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He, therefore, that refuses to do good to them whom he is bound to
love . . . is unnatural and <qex>monstrous</qex> in his affections.</q>
<rj><qau>Jer. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Extraordinary in a way to excite wonder, dislike,
apprehension, etc.; -- said of size, appearance, color, sound, etc.;
<as>as, a <ex>monstrous</ex> height; a <ex>monstrous</ex> ox; a
<ex>monstrous</ex> story.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Extraordinary on account of ugliness, viciousness,
or wickedness; hateful; horrible; dreadful.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So bad a death argues a <qex>monstrous</qex> life.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Abounding in monsters.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Where thou, perhaps, under the whelming tide⟦br⟧
Visitest the bottom of the <qex>monstrous</qex> world.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monstrous</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Monstrous
<hw>Mon"strous</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>Exceedingly; very; very
much.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>monstrous</xex> thick oil on the top.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And will be <qex>monstrous</qex> witty on the poor.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monstrously</ent>⟦br⟧
